\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b a}) Subsp. {\b spicata} (incl.{\i  V. hybrida} L.): stem more or less densely pubescent, usually glandular (rarely glabrous or sub-glabrous). Leaves linear-lanceolate to ovate, subsessile or the lower with petioles not more than 10 mm. Calyx more or less hairy, usually glandular; corolla clear blue, with ovate-lanceolate, flat lower lobes. 2n = 34, 68.{\i  Throughout the range of the species.}
