\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b d}) Subsp. {\b orchidea} (Crantz) Hayek in Hegi,{\i  Ill. Fl. Mitteleur.} {\b 6}({\b 1}): 46 (1913) ({\i V. orchidea} Crantz, {\i Pseudolysimachium spicatum} subsp.{\i  orchideum }(Crantz) Hartl): stem subglabrous below, more or less glandular-hirsute above. Leaves thick and rather shiny, subglabrous or sparsely hairy, the lower ovate to ovate-lanceolate, with petiole c. 1 mm. Calyx glandular-hairy; corolla pale blue, with lower lobes linear, twisted. 2n = 34.{\i  S.E. Europe, extending westwards to N. Italy and C. Czechoslovakia}. 
